      As Phil suggests, complex issues are one area where a citizens assembly makes sense.  Another area is where elected officials have a direct conflict of interest.  I've written extensively about this.  Check iSolon.org for a range of resources on citizens assembly based democratic reform, including the latest issue of the Citizens Assembly News Digest.<br/><br/>--J.H. Snider, President, iSolon.org

                  
